Genevieve Quintal, News24(Shutterstock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Four judges have been shortlisted and will be interviewed this week for the vacant position at the Constitutional Court.A position on the bench of the country's highest court, became vacant when Justice Thembile Skweyiya retired.The Judicial Service Commission will conduct the interviews for the position in Johannesburg on Thursday.All four shortlisted candidates are woman.The candidates are:- Justice Nonkosi Zoliswa Mhlantla;- Justice Leona Valerie Theron;- Judge Dhayanithie Pillay and;- Justice Zukisa Laura Lumka Tshiqi.On the same day, the JSC would also interview Jusitice Mandisa Muriel Lindelwa Maya for the vacant position of deputy president of the Supreme Court of Appeal.She was nominated by President Jacob Zuma.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.